MYSTIC_PC_0000_001.name: Guardian Palm - Mystic Skill
MYSTIC_PC_0000_001.desc: Find the Nightdream Monk in the northern section of Sundara Land to begin the Where a Thousand Buddhas Wept Side Story. Completing this quest will reward you with the Guardian Palm Mystic Art.
MYSTIC_PC_0000_001.details:
{
  "type": "Offensive, Area DMG",
  "tags": "Damage",
  "cost_tier4": "30 Vitality",
  "cooldown_tier4": "8 second(s)",
  "effect": "Unleash two palm strikes forward, then leap into the air and smite the ground to knock back nearby enemies. At 3-5m height, skill upgrades to Lamp Light with a 12s cooldown: Unleash palm strikes toward the ground and knocking back enemies in the area."
}

MYSTIC_PC_0000_002.name: Flaming Meteor - Mystic Skill
MYSTIC_PC_0000_002.desc: Interact with the 3 drums found in Boddhi Sea in Sundara Land to fight Ye Wanshan. After defeating the boss, you will gain access to its challenge version. Perform deflects against the challenge version of the boss to fill the eye meter beside its life bar. Filling the meter completely and defeating the boss will unlock the Flaming Meteor Mystic Art
MYSTIC_PC_0000_002.details:
{
  "type": "Offensive, Area DMG",
  "tags": "Damage",
  "cost_tier4": "60 Vitality",
  "cooldown_tier4": "30 second(s)",
  "effect": "Charge ahead and stomp the earth. Leap into the air, form a blazing spear and hurl it at your target, causing AoE explosion. Then crash down like a meteor for additional damage. Gain 15% Super Armor while casting."
}

MYSTIC_PC_0000_004.name: Lion's Roar (Part 2) - Mystic Skill
MYSTIC_PC_0000_004.desc: 2. Ring Bell. Found south of Buddha Fort which is in the northeast part of Qinghe.
MYSTIC_PC_0000_004.details:
{
  "type": "Offensive, Area Debuff",
  "tags": "Knockback",
  "cost_tier4": "30 Vitality",
  "cooldown_tier4": "12 second(s)",
  "effect": "Slam a giant bell, then unleash a deafening roar, dealing damage over 14 hits in a large area. Gain 15% Damage Reduction and Fortitude. Hitting a Toad Venom target detonates the venom, spreading it and increasing roar damage."
}

MYSTIC_PC_0000_005.name: Tai Chi - Mystic Skill
MYSTIC_PC_0000_005.desc: After unlocking the map by speaking to the Verdant Wilds Wayfarer in Qinghe, you'll encounter a bear reaching for a beehive. Observing the bear initiates the first Skill Theft mini-game, which rewards you with Tai Chi upon completion.
MYSTIC_PC_0000_005.details:
{
  "type": "Offensive, Puzzle",
  "tags": "Tai Chi, Shield Breaker",
  "cost_tier4": "",
  "cooldown_tier4": "",
  "effect": "Out of Combat: Gathers fallen leaves in certain areas, and creates ripples on water that cause fish to leap. In Combat: Pulls and whirls targets, allowing aiming by rotating the camera, then hurls them for damage. Especially effective against Shield-Bearing enemies."
}

MYSTIC_PC_0000_006.name: Leaping Toad - Mystic Skill
MYSTIC_PC_0000_006.desc: Talk to the man jumping like a toad near the southwest exit of General's Shrine. He will ask you to observe the toad beside him. Successfully complete the Skill Theft mini-game to acquire the Leaping Toad Mystic Skill.
MYSTIC_PC_0000_006.details:
{
  "type": "Offensive, Area Debuff",
  "tags": "Damage",
  "cost_tier4": "25 Vitality",
  "cooldown_tier4": "8 second(s)",
  "effect": "Flip back to knock back and damage enemies, then lunge to apply Toad Venom. The third cast becomes Golden Toad Crash, a knockdown AoE slam. Toad Venom: Explodes after 5 seconds or on death and can be detonated by Lion's Roar."
}

MYSTIC_PC_0000_007.name: Lion's Roar (Part 1) - Mystic Skill
MYSTIC_PC_0000_007.desc: 1. Ring the Bell. Found on the west wall of General's Shrine

MYSTIC_PC_0000_008.name: Lion's Roar (Part 3) - Mystic Skill
MYSTIC_PC_0000_008.desc: 3.Ring the Bell. On top of the hill south of General's Shrine

MYSTIC_PC_0000_009.name: Cloud Step - Mystic Skill
MYSTIC_PC_0000_009.desc: You will unlock Cloud Steps during the Echoes in the Shrine quest, which takes you into the underground area beneath Generalâs Shrine. The scroll for the Cloud Steps skill can be found on a corpse located just before the long stairway as part of the quest objectives.
MYSTIC_PC_0000_009.details:
{
  "type": "Offensive, Puzzle",
  "tags": "Lightness Skill, Undercut",
  "cost_tier4": "",
  "cooldown_tier4": "",
  "effect": "Out of Combat: Leap high and slam down, or hold breath to jump to marked spots. In Combat: Stomp on an enemy's shoulder to deal Physical Damage; deals additional Attribute Damage effective against Cavalry and units with Unstable Poise."
}

MYSTIC_PC_0000_010.name: Calestial Seize - Mystic Skill
MYSTIC_PC_0000_010.details:
{
  "type": "Offensive, Puzzle",
  "tags": "Take Item, Disarm",
  "cost_tier4": "",
  "cooldown_tier4": "",
  "effect": "Out of Combat: Pulls distant objects, including items from chests and backpacks. In Combat: Disarms an enemy and counters using their own weapon to deal Physical Damage, other Attribute Damage, and Qi Damage. Damage scales with the weapon's weight."
}

MYSTIC_PC_0000_011.name: Meridian Touch - Mystic Skill
MYSTIC_PC_0000_011.desc: On the path between Generalâs Shrine and Heavenâs Pier, you will encounter Yan Qiren, a man who appears to have turned to stone. This will start the Meridian Touch quest. Speak to him to learn the Meridian Touch skill, then use it on him to release him and complete the quest.
MYSTIC_PC_0000_011.details:
{
  "type": "Offensive, Puzzle",
  "tags": "Acupoint Strike, Qi Breaking",
  "cost_tier4": "",
  "cooldown_tier4": "",
  "effect": "Out of Combat: Select Acupoints for a chance at special effects to immobilize a target (Fleetfoot: Yangbai â immobilize; Clarity: Xiaohu â uncontrollable laughter; Unfettered Flow: Quchi â unbearable itching). In Combat: Chance to immobilize, deal Physical damage, and break Vital Points. Immobilize ineffective against mighty enemies. Breaking Vital Points disables Qi regen and deals extra Physical and Qi damage."
}

MYSTIC_PC_0000_012.name: Drunken Poet - Mystic Skill
MYSTIC_PC_0000_012.desc: Drinking enough wine from the Honest Merchant unlocks the Drunken Poet Mystic Skill. This NPC is first located in Blissful Retreat, but later relocates to Harvestfall Village as the story progresses. Purchase and drink the wine he sells until you receive both the âWastedâ debuff and the âAlcohol Poisoningâ illness. The process is random but typically requires around 8 bottles. To recover quickly, you can visit the Evercare Clinic to heal the debuff.
MYSTIC_PC_0000_012.details:
{
  "type": "Offensive, Single-target Burst",
  "tags": "Damage",
  "cost_tier4": "10 Vitality",
  "cooldown_tier4": "0.1 second(s)",
  "effect": "Drink to enter the Intoxicated state, imitating the Poet Immortal. Can cast repeatedly for up to 5 strikes, each consuming 6 Vitality. Intoxicated lasts 30s. Dragon's Breath and Drunken Poet can be used without drinking while Intoxicated."
}

MYSTIC_PC_0000_013.name: Safe Mighty Drop - Mystic Skill
MYSTIC_PC_0000_013.desc: Safe Mighty Drop is a first-time reward for clearing the Mysterious Outpost in the western section of Moonveil Mountain.
MYSTIC_PC_0000_013.details:
{
  "type": "Movement, Movement (Sub-type)",
  "tags": "Lightness Skill",
  "cost_tier4": "",
  "cooldown_tier4": "",
  "effect": "After leaping with Threefold Skywalk, interrupt your current movement with a rapid landing."
}

MYSTIC_PC_0000_014.name: Thousand Mile Flight - Mystic Skill
MYSTIC_PC_0000_014.details:
{
  "type": "Movement, Lightness",
  "tags": "Lightness Skill",
  "cost_tier4": "15 Vitality",
  "cooldown_tier4": "1 second(s)",
  "effect": "All major factions restrict lightness skills. Gain faction keepsakes by increasing Exploration to move freely. Soaring like a dragon across the sky, leaving traces a thousand miles."
}

MYSTIC_PC_0000_015.desc: 4. Ring the Bell. Found in an abandoned residence in Witherwilds

MYSTIC_PC_0000_017.name: Veil of Stillness - Mystic Skill
MYSTIC_PC_0000_017.desc: After reaching Level 8, a Skill Theft encounter unlocks southeast of Moonveil Peak. Speak to Qiu Yuehai to begin the quest, then hide behind the large boulder between him and the master to initiate the Skill Theft mini-game. Succeed to obtain the Veil of Stillness Mystic Skill.

{

  "tags": "Stealth",
  "cost_tier4": "20 Vitality",
  "cooldown_tier4": "30 second(s)",
  "effect": "Activating this art steadies your breath and reduces your presence, making you less detectable by enemies for a short time. This technique is purely for stealthâif direct combat begins, the illusion immediately fails."
}

MYSTIC_PC_0000_018.name: Blinding Mist - Mystic Skill
MYSTIC_PC_0000_018.desc: You will earn the Blinding Mist Mystic Art by completing the Blind to the World Side Story. Begin this quest by speaking to Unfated Tian near the deep lake in the east section of the Moonveil Mountain area.
MYSTIC_PC_0000_018.details:
{

  "tags": "Assassination",
  "cost_tier4": "70 Vitality",
  "cooldown_tier4": "45 second(s)",
  "effect": "Releases poisonous mist in front of you to block enemy vision and deal damage, making them blind and unable to fight for 5 seconds. During this time, Touch of Death can be used to subdue the target. Ineffective against mighty enemies."
}

MYSTIC_PC_0000_020.name: Touch of Death - Mystic Skill
MYSTIC_PC_0000_020.desc: Find the ruined fortess near the Battlecrest Slope in the Verdant Wilds to start the Echoes of Old Battles Side Story. Follow the clues to get the Warrior's Pledge deep underground and learn the Touch of Death Mystic Art.
MYSTIC_PC_0000_020.details:
{

  "cost_tier4": "",

}
